    "explanation": "Probability measures the likelihood of events. P(A) = favorable outcomes / total outcomes. For independent events: P(A\u2229B) = P(A)\u00b7P(B). Conditional probability: P(A|B) = P(A\u2229B)/P(B). Bayes' theorem reverses conditioning: P(A|B) = P(B|A)\u00b7P(A)/P(B). Expected value E[X] = \u03a3 x\u00b7P(X=x) is the 'average' outcome. Variance measures spread: Var(X) = E[X\u00b2] - (E[X])\u00b2.",
